IGF::OT::IGF CHARLEROI RIVER CHAMBER COMPLETION MOD A00003, CHANGE AE, EVALUATE AND ANALYZE BP EFFLUENT DATA. THE WORK TO BE PERFORMED UNDER THIS MODIFICATION INCLUDES PROVISION FOR THE CONTRACTOR TO EVALUATE AND ANALYZE ALL EXISTING SAMPLE DATA AND EFFLUENT DISCHARGE DATA AND DEVELOP, AS APPROPRIATE, TREATMENT OPTIONS AND RECOMMENDATION TO MEET EFFLUENT STANDARDS FOR THE LEFT BANK CONCRETE BATCH PLANT. THIS MODIFICATION IS CONSISTENT WITH PART 1.7.1.1 (NPDES PERMITS FOR STORMWATER/WASTEWATER DISCHARGES) OF SECTION 01 57 20.00 10 ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS AND INCLUDES THE FOLLOWING SPECIFIC TASKS/MILESTONES: (1) DATA REVIEW - REVIEW EXISTING SAMPLE DATA PROVIDED BY USACE-PITTSBURGH FOR IMP 101 AND OUTFALL 001 COLLECTED SINCE THE NPDES PERMIT WAS ISSUED IN FEBRUARY 2014. CONFIRM ALL TEST RESULTS STATED IN DMR ARE IN COMPLIANCE WITH PERMIT REQUIREMENTS. ALSO, REVIEW EXISTING EFFLUENT DISCHARGE DATA PROVIDED BY USACE PITTSBURGH FOR OUTFALL 002 COLLECTED ON A MONTHLY BASIS SINCE MARCH 2015. BASED ON CHARACTERIZATION AND ANALYSIS OF SAMPLE DATA, DETERMINE AND JUSTIFY THE NEED FOR A TREATMENT SYSTEM TO COMPLY WITH NPDES PERMIT REQUIREMENTS APPLICABLE TO OUTFALL 002. SUMMARIZE RESULTS OF THE DATA REVIEW IN A MEMORANDUM TO USACE-PITTSBURGH. COMPLETE BY 2 SEPTEMBER 2016. (2) DEVELOPMENT OF TREATEMENT SYSTEM OPTIONS (AS APPLICABLE) - IF A TREATMENT SYSTEM IS REQUIRED TO TREAT STORMWATER AND SEEP IN CHANNEL TO OUTFALL 002, A PLAN SHALL BE DEVELOPED AND A PROPOSAL PROVIDED FOR UP TO FOUR (4) TREATMENT SYSTEM OPTIONS. ALL TREATMENT OPTIONS SHALL INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING DESIGN CONTRAINTS: (A) PROVIDE PROTECTION OF TREATMENT SYSTEM FROM PERIODIC FLOODING THAT OCCURS AT THE BATCH PLANT BULKHEAD AND/OR PLACE TREATMENT SYSTEM OUTSIDE OF THE FLOOD ZONE (B) PROVIDE PROTECTION OF TREATMENT SYSTEM AGAINST VANDALISM (C) SYSTEM MUST BE COMPATIBLE WITH CURRENT OPERATION OF THE BATCH PLANT ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION SYSTEMS COMPLETE BY 1 OCTOBER 2016. (3) PREPARATION OF REPORT (AS APPLICABLE) - PROVIDE A REPORT TO USACE-PITTSBURGH WITH DETAILS OF EACH TREATMENT OPTION AND COST FOR OUTFALL 002. PROVIDE RECOMMENDATION FOR SELECTION OF THE PREFERRED TREATMENT PLAN. COMPLETE BY 15 OCTOBER 2016. (4) SELECTION OF PREFERRED TREATMENT SYSTEM (AS APPLICABLE) - ATTEND A MEETING AND PROVIDE A PRESENTATION TO USACE-PITTSBURGH DETAILING PROPOSED TREATMENT OPTIONS AND RECOMMENDED TREATMENT SYSTEM FOR OUTFALL 002. CONTRACTOR SHALL BE AVAILABLE TO ANSWER QUESTIONS AND/OR PROVIDE CLARIFICATION TO USACE-PITTSBURGH AS REQUIRED. COMPLETE BY 1 NOVEMBER 2016.
